HOWL PHYS-24: GENERATION DEMOCRACY AND THE BOSON PROBLEM
======================================================================

BETA COEFFICIENT DECOMPOSITION (Level 1, exact)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Gauge self-coupling: b_i^gauge = -(11/3) * C_2(G_i)
      b_1^gauge = -(11/3)*0                0.0
      b_2^gauge = -(11/3)*2 = -22/3        -7.3333333333
      b_3^gauge = -(11/3)*3 = -11          -11.0

  Higgs doublet (1,2,1/2):
      b_1^Higgs = 1/10                     0.1
      b_2^Higgs = 1/6                      0.16666666667
      b_3^Higgs = 0                        0.0

  One complete fermion generation:
      b_1^gen = 4/3                        1.3333333333
      b_2^gen = 4/3                        1.3333333333
      b_3^gen = 4/3                        1.3333333333

  THIS IS GENERATION DEMOCRACY.
  Every complete generation contributes identically to all three
  gauge couplings. The contribution is (4/3, 4/3, 4/3).

  Three generations (n_gen = 3):
      b_1^fermion = 3 * 4/3 = 4            4.0
      b_2^fermion = 3 * 4/3 = 4            4.0
      b_3^fermion = 3 * 4/3 = 4            4.0

VERIFICATION: DECOMPOSITION SUMS TO SM BETAS
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  b_1: gauge + Higgs + fermion = 41/10     4.1
  b_1 from library = 41/10                 4.1

  b_2: gauge + Higgs + fermion = -19/6     -3.1666666667
  b_2 from library = -19/6                 -3.1666666667

  b_3: gauge + Higgs + fermion = -7        -7.0
  b_3 from library = -7                    -7.0

THE BOSON PROBLEM
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Gap ratio numerator (b1 - b2):
      gauge:   22/3                        7.3333333333
      Higgs:   -1/15                       -0.066666666667
      fermion: 0                           0.0

  Gap ratio denominator (b2 - b3):
      gauge:   11/3                        3.6666666667
      Higgs:   1/6                         0.16666666667
      fermion: 0                           0.0

  Fermion contribution to numerator: 0
  Fermion contribution to denominator: 0
  BOTH ZERO. Fermions are invisible to the gap ratio.

  Gap ratio (gauge + Higgs only) = 218/115 1.8956521739
  Gap ratio (full SM) = 218/115            1.8956521739

  Percentage of gap numerator (b1 - b2 = 109/15):
      gauge  (%%)                          100.91743119
      Higgs  (%%)                          -0.91743119266
      fermion (%%)                         0.0

  Percentage of gap denominator (b2 - b3 = 23/6):
      gauge  (%%)                          95.652173913
      Higgs  (%%)                          4.347826087
      fermion (%%)                         0.0

  Pure-gauge gap ratio (no Higgs, no fermions):
      = 2                                  2.0
  The Higgs shifts this from 2 to 218/115 = 1.896.
  Fermions shift it by exactly 0.

  The SM unification failure is a BOSON PROBLEM.
  Fixing it requires changing the bosonic content —
  either adding new gauge bosons (MSSM) or adding a
  representation that breaks the fermion democracy
  (the Cabibbo Doublet).

